==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[παύσις]]''' (''pausis'') "the cease of an action, temporarily or permanently", from '''[[παύω]]''' (''pavo''), "to stop, to cease, to put an end to something temporarily or permanently".

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: pôz
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /pɔːz/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /pO:z/

====Homophones====
*[[paws]]
*[[pores]] (non-rhotic accents)
*[[pours]] (non-rhotic accents)

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|paus|e}}

# To interrupt current work and do something else for a moment.

